  "original_title": "\u0d91\u0d9a\u0dca\u0dc3\u0dca\u0db4\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0dc3\u0dca \u0db4\u0dbb\u0dca\u0dbd\u0dca \u0dc0\u0db1\u0dca\u0daf\u0dd2\u0dba \u0dbb\u0dd4\u0db4\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dbd\u0dca \u0db6\u0dd2\u0dbd\u0dd2\u0dba\u0db1 1.3 \u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Express Pearl compensation is Rs 1.3 billion",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Ms. Darshanee Lahadapura, Chairperson of the Maritime Environment Protection Authority, said that the general treasury has received an amount of 1.3 billion rupees from the ship's insurance company for cleaning up the beach by removing plastic and waste released from the sinking of the Express Pearl ship.",
        "She said that the cabinet paper submitted requesting 903,857,293 rupees from the treasury to settle the payment related to beach cleaning has been approved.",
        "Mrs. Lahadapura also said that the first interim report has been sent to the Australian Bar Association after calculating the environmental damage caused to the coastline and coastline due to the Express Pearl container ship that sank in Sri Lankan waters on May 20 last year while carrying goods under the Singapore flag. .",
        "She also mentioned that after receiving the instructions from that institution, further legal steps will be taken together with the Attorney General's Department."
      ],
